content: Great graphic, gameplay... Love it...please new levels...
Short and sweet

Intuitive puzzle gameplay that does a great job of introducing new mechanics and then integrating them into old ones. Long enough to really explore the ways each mechanic can be used, and then doesn't overstay it's welcome.
Addictive puzzle game. Requires more levels to make it more challenging. I completed the 90 levels within a couple of days of downloading but very entertaining and very nicely created.
A lot of fun. Like sudokus but less boring
Fun

Note that the game doesn't save your progress while playing a level! So with the bigger ones later on, be sure that you don't interrupt! Pretty presentation and an interesting puzzle mechanic but it is not explained what the head on the top right does and after solving bonus levels, nothing happens. No congratulations, no animation, no unlocking of something - it's just for your own gratification.
The game seems like a fun distraction so far, but the frame rate is really not what it should be on a OnePlus 7 Pro with 90hz display.
Excellent game, only gripe is that it's too short.
Great game, candy eye smooth interface. But needs updating.

A really enjoyable puzzle. The incremental increase in challenge flowed so well, never stalling you for too long and throwing in a new idea just as you need something to keep you engaged. Well done developers. Happy to pay for this quality. More levels would have been appreciated. Both me at nearly 50 and my mathsy 8 year old enjoyed it.
Nice and beautiful puzzle game about summing pieces with small amounts.
Very enjoyable so far, reminds me of Hexcells on the pc but with some newer mechanics to keep it interesting!
Good game but to much time for updates
excellent game, sadly only 90 levels... waiting for "Hexologic 2" :)
Perfect puzzler for in-between meetings or on the train. The only downside is the limited amount of puzzles.
Very fun, especially for the price. Plus no ads.

Absolutely loved playing this. Really well designed puzzles tested my deduction skills. This is one of my top 3 mobile puzzle games. The UI was also really helpful, intuitive and easy to understand. I wanted to mark hexes with possible answers so I instinctively long pressed a hex and that opened the marking menu. At any point in a level there is always at least one hex that you can figure out with the information you have. Can't wait for more levels or another game from these designers!
Entertaining but not particularly challenging so far (roughly 50 levels in).
I really enjoyed the experience. It's a wonderful take on sudoku and I wish there were more levels, more puzzles and more rule sets.

It's okay for a few levels but doesn't captivate me. I guess the best compliment is that what it does, it does well. However, there are many other games (including free ones) if rather be playing. Uninstalled.
Great game, but why no achievements?
Awesome numbers puzzle game with a great art style
This game is too good for Google Play. Most other games on Google Play are crooked just like its retard editor! Will never purchase another cent.
Loved this game - one of my favourite puzzle games on Android. Really satisfying to work out a solution and solve the puzzle. Wish there were more levels!
Lacks cloud saves and landscape layout
Exceptionally polished puzzle game with enough challenge to keep you interested.
Quite a fun game, although a bit easy in highlight-mode and a bit hard in the other mode. Looks and sounds good. Shame it doesn't last long.
A solid logic puzzle game with a focus on mental addition. Not my kind of puzzle game tough, due to most puzzels not including creative problem solving only logical thinking.
Finished the game right away. Hoping there could be more levels in the next update.

One of my favourite games I've played on a phone. Hard to describe how fun the gameplay is; it's challenging but not in a maddening, infuriating way, it's almost instinctive how you solve each puzzle and the sense of satisfaction is huge. Not the longest game in the world, but not the most expensive either and wholly worth every penny. Graphics are lovely and the soundtrack and sfx are bang on. Hats off to to the team for a wonderful game. :)
Really nice presentation, but way too short and very little (if any) replay value. However, I payed some 60 cents for it ...
A bit too short and easy, even on the harder mode. Would pay for more level packs! Very good while it lasted.
Way too short, completed it in a morning... More levels please!
very well made, minimalist design and goergeous art and audio direction. I really liked the red (hard) mode, it made the game shine for me.
Hints would be nice. Otherwise a great game

the only reason i am giving four instead of five stars is because there is only 90 levels and maybe 20 bonus levels TOPS. i completed all of these within like three days... i think there should be more levels. other than that... the background music is relaxing, they ease into the new math slowly which is nice so you aren't thrown off. easy to use for the most part, and a fun and somewhat challenging game! i highly recommend. just wish there were more levels! hopefully more to come soon!! :)
Best game ever ... but really the creator of the game is obsessed in Math :) sure he/she is an A+ student

Brilliant game, loved the mechanic, nice amount of levels. The menu background parallax is beautifully made. Since I played similar puzzles before (Kakuro) the early levels unravel quite fast after applying some easy distribution rules, but once the connected tiles and conditions come in, it gets really interesting. Overall, great game, good work! I loved it! :)
Fun little numbers game. Felt short, with 90 levels +bonus, but I enjoyed it.
A really excellent little puzzler. I really hope more levels or a sequel come out at some point.
Fun but easy. Please add more games
Excellent!
Relaxing!

I just played through it a second time. Why? Because as far as logic puzzles go, it's a modern classic. It resembles kakuro a bit, but it's different enough to stand on its own. The rules and controls are simple but has much depth. My only gripe, as others have said, is that just over 100 puzzles just has you wanting more of them. Is almost a bonus, but nevertheless : the graphics and music are pretty soothing, and therefore ideal for this kind of game. All in all : ABSOLUTELY worth it.
Clever and fun.

The only problem with this game is that there aren't more levels. That's not to say that the content doesn't justify the price, rather it's a shame that I no longer have new levels to look forward to. This game is essential for anybody who likes puzzles. The mechanics progress at a nice pace, the interface is clean despite the amount of information it needs to convey, and the backdrops have tons of fun colourful details to enjoy as you make the climb.
This game is amazing. I need more. Beat the whole game. The last boss level was insane. It took me 20 min an about 7 restarts. Pls add more levels.
A bit short but beautiful and well designed puzzles.
Relatively simple mechanics but it does evolve over the levels. It would be nice if there was a settings menu or a sound toggle though.
Very fun and engaging! Hopefully we can get added levels in the future because it's not super long.
Wonderful! Please make more games!
Great idea, kickass puzzles, great music, brilliant level progression. Loved the app. Must try if you love number puzzles
Great game just wish there were more levels
Fun but finished way too fast.

This is a fantastic puzzle game! I got many hours out of it and recon I'll pay through it again. There are some very clever ideas introduced throughout to keep it interesting. I love the minimal style, though wish I'd learned you can hold press on tiles for more options, rather than just teasing to cycle through the basic options. I hope we see more levels one day!
Challenging puzzles and smart mechanics make for a perfect time-killer. Definitely worth its price.
excellent, beautiful, thoughtful game, can't wait to make all my friends try it!
Great game, but a little short. Could use more levels.

A deceptively fiendish game - shows you a simple process to begin with as an introduction to each type of puzzle, then let's you work it out for yourself, so much so it feels so natural.  I LOVED it!  But I do have one issue, a minor one but an issue.  Not enough levels - i completed both the green mode and red mode along with the locked levels in a day.  I know that there is no facility of an endless puzzle generator, but more levels would be nice, or as a long shot, maybe the facility of being able to generate levels and submitting them for others to try.  Well worth the money!

Game is great! Loved the puzzle! Took one star because game has a problem saving your progress, sometimes you open it and you have to do some levels again... and it sucks. Also, please add achievements to this game!
Good but too short.
great game. had bought it on iOS and re-bought it for my new Android phone.
Very well done math puzzles. Just as you're about to feel the game becoming easy, it jumps difficulty on you. drives you to want to know what new challenge it will provide you. Must play!
superb & one of a kind. please add more levels, I just can't believe that I finished all 90 levels in both mode modes üôÉ
was a pretty sweet little brain game. very well made.
love the game! a few hours of fun for a small prize.
Loved everything, but even on red (hard?) it's too easy and too short. Please give us more!
Demoed it for the Nintendo Switch version since it's on dicount and actually cheaper than this mobile version for once. Seems legit. Thanks for the demo. Refunding now to buy that one.
Noooo ive finished all 90 plus the bonus ones and i still want more. i love this game. very fun calm and comfortable. now what am i going to play xD

The only one-mechanic puzzler I have ever finished. After 30 levels or so, this type of games bore me: OK, now is the same thing a bit more twisted each time for 70 levels more! But this game, the transitioning scenery, the transitioning music! (that last is incredible, I opened the game only to listen to it!) really got me to enjoy until the end. Never have I seen a game like this. Edit: Today I was furious because of work, finally got to relax and sleep opening the game. Thank you, really :)
Cascading deduction with simple arithmetic. Good but not great. (review based on 60+ levels)

Puzzle game worth the buy. Whether you just want to pass some time or are interested in developing your logical reasoning skills, you will probably enjoy this game. Levels are organized into worlds that have unique themes and each introduce a new mechanic. The masterfully integrated music compliments these worlds by changing subtly as you scroll through the scenery. The controls are simple and the levels of difficulty are well defined. A free version and Play Store achievements would be nice.

It's a great game, nice gameplay but also beautiful design. I'm really hoping you'll be adding even more levels - can't really complain about not enough content since there are a lot of levels already, but I couldn't put it down, and played through all of them in no time at all!
too easy and no story

Fun app, eases you into it over the first levels but had some really nice challenging puzzles when you get into it. New mechanics change things up to give new challenges as you go along. Beautiful style. Definitely worth the price!!!
I found this game on Switch. i have to say I'm not a fan of the Android experience. But this game is definitely addicting. I could play it for hours.
this game is really, really excellent but every time i exit i have to go back and do a level or two over again, it doesn't save your progress very accurately

I like the idea and the concept, that was well executed and kept me going. The downside is that the levels were way too easy. Basically once it started to get challenging, the game ended. Would love some sequel or more levels with increased difficulty. Well done!
Fun puzzle/logic game. I really enjoyed the levels with the comparers.
needs more levels!

Excellent & unique puzzler. Hoping for many more levels in the future! There are a little more than 100, which are made much more challenging with completion being able to be hidden until you're totally done. Highly recommend.
90 levels. Can plow true in 2h. Good game!
No landscape mode. So annoying
good puzzle game. but always desiring new levels
wonderful game play fantastic interface. For me way to easy. Only level 89 challeged me there are 90 levels in all. In all it took maybe 4 hours in total for me to finish.

it plays like a mix of star battle and sudoku and it's just perfect! pay once and get the whole game, so no scummy IAPs! honestly, this is worth more than a dollar! wish I could have spent more for it and that's not something I say very often. if you like good puzzle games pick this one up! good job, devs!
Mix between Minesweeper and Sudoku. Nice atmosphere.
one of the greatest
This game is wonderful! I like the concept!
Amazing game. Can't wait for more updates, new mechanics and more awesome illustration. A gem in the play store.
Relaxing, simple and beautiful!
Its a very great game. Feels something like sudoku. Really loved it. I hope new levels are added soon.
Great game! I would suggest a save feature. I've already lost progress multiple times on a few levels.

Simple concept but brilliantly executed, gameplay is so smooth and addictive. Love the UI design and the background art is just gorgeous! I only have one similar complaint to most people, I already finished all 90 main levels and most extra levels in 3 days :(. I think at this point I wouldn't want any new mechanic but more generic levels that combines all the existing mechanics would be really nice to have. Can't wait for more updates!
Great game without IAP and playable offline. Relaxing yet there is enough challenge if you are looking for it.
Excellent game - not long enough
This is an amazing puzzle game. I would recommend this to many people. The only problem is that I feel like there should be more puzzles. I would love an update with more puzzles.
Loda jevi game 6e

Fun little puzzle game. New rules for the puzzles are introduced in a nice way. I had fun getting through the main 90 levels and am working on the extras as well. I'm hoping there are plans for more levels.
Please check if level 67 have any problem or not . I am unable to find any solution.
Good, but short.
My phone softlocks 4 out of 5 timen when I try to open the game, forcing me to reboot my phone.
This game is fantastic. It's a whole new take on abstract games and it is beautiful, both visually and intelligently. One of the best games I've ever played.
Good but need some improvements
hi i have completed all 90 levels within a week.. can you please add new levels every week
Excellent mathematic picross style number filling game. Plenty of relatively simple levels that you'll enjoy solving. I definitely recommend this game
replyContent: It's great to hear that you enjoyed the game :) We've just released a big content update with 36 new levels and a brand new difficulty level!

content: Level 60 is bugged. Vertical is supposed to be 17 not 15

Absolutely love the game. Only one complaint... it drains the battery pretty bad. Wish I could turn on a power saving mode. There are a lot of background animations that run which I would turn off if it saved battery.

I love everything about this game. It scratches my picross itch harder than most picross games, somehow. Content is very very light though and I hope that improves. Devs, please allow us to mute sounds in addition to music! Edit: Devs are clearly awesome! I just went ahead and bought the Switch version as well üòÅ
replyContent: It's great to hear that you enjoyed the game :) We've just released a big content update with 36 new levels and a brand new difficulty level! We have also added new options for the sounds.

content: Good puzzle game. A mix between Picross and Sudoku. Great fun but only 60 levels and 15 bonus levels. Some only take a couple minutes to beat. Edit: They recently updated the game with more levels and difficulty.
replyContent: It's great to hear that you enjoyed the game :) We've just released a big content update with 36 new levels and a brand new difficulty level!

content: Nice game

Amazing game. Gameplay is superb, although only really challenging towards the end. Graphics are beautiful. Very short, only 75 levels that cane be done in a couple of hours. Too bad that there isn't a random level generator. All in all recommended, it's well worth the price.

I enjoyed it very much. But once you beat the main levels you get the credits, so naturally you move on to the last of the bonus levels then there's just nothing. All you get is the abrupt realisation that the game is now over.

Great puzzle game that will make you think. The concept of adding numbers in each hex "row" is simple enough and with a few minor mechanics thrown in, this game proves to be super interesting. I just wish there was more. A daily challenge would be great or even just extra levels later would bring me back easy.
Fun ! And absolutely gorgeous !
Albeit short, for the $1 i payed for I got very pleasing math puzzles
I really enjoyed this game. I was quite sad when I saw I was nearing the end of the levels, I hope they make more levels. Definitely worth buying, had a great time solving these puzzles!

wormkeally really liked the game. Would be a 5 stars if I would not have completed it in 2 hours. A little bit too short for a paid game in my opinion. I wish you're still working on new levels. Keep up the good work devs <3
replyContent: It's great to hear that you enjoyed the game :) We've just released a big content update with 36 new levels and a brand new difficulty level!

content: A bit short in some ways, but at least it didn't seem endless. Fun game
A new take on a sudoku style puzzle, with stylish graphics, calming music and great gameplay and controls. Hope to see even more levels in an update or sequel perhaps. Great work.

I loved the fast, puzzling, and challenging Aesthetic of the vast variety of levels the game introduces early on. But sadly your journey ends in roughly two to three hours, their ideas of tiring to mix four different games/concepts into one mobile app makes the later levels feel uneventful and boring at best. I wanted to still give this app five stars as I got my money worth, also the sweet visuals the games offers is just a bonus added on with a killer soundtrack! I would definitely see this game being a fan favorite amongst family and friend alike. Lastly the controls were flawless making my experience worth the ninitynine cent.
Good game, enjoyed it.
I found this rather boring & too repetitive

A lovely relaxing puzzle game with great graphics and visuals. The controls 
are intuitive and it's nice that you can actually finish the game in a 
reasonable time, though I'd happily pay to unlock an additional set of 
puzzles!

How do I mute all sounds on this game? The sound button only disables 
music. Very annoying.
replyContent: It's great to hear that you enjoyed the game :) We've just released a big content update with 36 new levels and a brand new difficulty level! You can mute the sounds as well now!

content: Very fun game; great adaptation of Sudoku. Super engaging.
Crazy awesome game

Simple to pick up but engaging at the same time. As other reviews mention, 
the sixty levels (and bonus levels) go by quickly. Hopefully more levels 
are available later.

Interesting number puzzle game. However not enough variety and at 60 levels 
(some take less than a minute to finish) plus 15 bonus levels, game is to 
short. Worth the price for a days play.

content:
60+15 levels of great fun. Not very long but no advertisements, which is a

Simple, relaxing. Nice design. It seemed a bit short. Easy to miss the 
bonus games after completing the 60! Never difficult. Well worth the play.

content:
A fun puzzle game, but I finished all of the levels within a couple of 
hours. Hopefully the devs will be looking to add more in.

content:
I like this game but it's really easy. The entire game took me about 30 
minutes to beat it at a really casual speed. Without more content in not 
sure I could give it a higher score. If a procedurally generated set of 
levels were available it would add more replayability. It's worth the 0.99 
but I can't say I'll be coming back to play this without lots more levels.

content: Best logic game ever!!!

Latest update fixed all issues. Thanks! Fun game. I can already see wanting 
more levels

content: Perfect logic game woth great graphics ^^ love it <3
Nice game, really well presented, but possibly a little easy.
